```python
{
    "question": "The probability it will rain on Saturday is $60\%$, and the probability it will rain on Sunday is $25\%$. If it rains on Saturday, the probability that it will also rain on Sunday increases to $50\%$. What is the probability it will rain on both days, expressed as a percent?",
    "answer": "First, let's define the probabilities given in the problem. The probability it will rain on Saturday is $P(\text{Saturday}) = 0.60$. The probability it will rain on Sunday given that it rained on Saturday is $P(\text{Sunday}|\text{Saturday}) = 0.50$. The probability it will rain on both days is given by the formula for conditional probability: $P(\text{Saturday and Sunday}) = P(\text{Saturday}) \times P(\text{Sunday}|\text{Saturday})$. Plugging in the values, we get: $P(\text{Saturday and Sunday}) = 0.60 \times 0.50 = 0.30$. Converting this to a percent, we get $0.30 \times 100 = 30\%$. The answer is: 30.000"
}
```

